#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/mixins.py:docstring of
#: spack.mixins.filter_compiler_wrappers:10
msgid ""
"This is useful for packages that register the path to the compiler they are "
"built with to be used later at runtime. Spack's compiler wrappers cannot be "
"used at runtime, as they require Spack's build environment to be set up. "
"Using this function, the compiler wrappers are replaced with the actual "
"compilers, so that the package works correctly at runtime."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/mixins.py:docstring of
#: spack.mixins.filter_compiler_wrappers:15
msgid ""
"files to be filtered relative to the search root (install prefix by default)."
