#: spack.spec.Spec.format:3
msgid ""
"Using an ``{attribute}`` format specifier, any field of the spec can be "
"selected. Those attributes can be recursive. For example, ``s."
"format({compiler.version})`` will print the version of the compiler."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/spec.py:docstring of
#: spack.spec.Spec.format:7
msgid ""
"If the attribute in a format specifier evaluates to ``None``, then the "
"format specifier will evaluate to the empty string, ``\"\"``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/spec.py:docstring of
#: spack.spec.Spec.format:10
msgid "Commonly used attributes of the Spec for format strings include:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/spec.py:docstring of
#: spack.spec.Spec.format:12
msgid ""
"name\n"
"version\n"
"compiler_flags\n"
"compilers\n"
"variants\n"
"architecture\n"
"architecture.platform\n"
"architecture.os\n"
"architecture.target\n"
"prefix\n"
"namespace"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/spec.py:docstring of
#: spack.spec.Spec.format:26
msgid "Some additional special-case properties can be added:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/spec.py:docstring of
#: spack.spec.Spec.format:28
msgid ""
"hash[:len]    The DAG hash with optional length argument\n"
"spack_root    The spack root directory\n"
"spack_install The spack install directory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/spec.py:docstring of
#: spack.spec.Spec.format:34
msgid ""
"The ``^`` sigil can be used to access dependencies by name. ``s.format({^mpi."
"name})`` will print the name of the MPI implementation in the spec."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/spec.py:docstring of
#: spack.spec.Spec.format:38
msgid ""
"The ``@``, ``%``, and ``/`` sigils can be used to include the sigil with the "
"printed string. These sigils may only be used with the appropriate "
"attributes, listed below:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/spec.py:docstring of
#: spack.spec.Spec.format:42
msgid "``@``: ``{@version}``, ``{@compiler.version}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/spec.py:docstring of
#: spack.spec.Spec.format:43
msgid "``%``: ``{%compiler}``, ``{%compiler.name}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/spec.py:docstring of
#: spack.spec.Spec.format:44
msgid "``/``: ``{/hash}``, ``{/hash:7}``, etc"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/spec.py:docstring of
#: spack.spec.Spec.format:46
msgid ""
"The ``@`` sigil may also be used for any other property named ``version``. "
"Sigils printed with the attribute string are only printed if the attribute "
"string is non-empty, and are colored according to the color of the attribute."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/spec.py:docstring of
#: spack.spec.Spec.format:50
msgid ""
"Variants listed by name naturally print with their sigil. For example, "
"``spec.format(\"{variants.debug}\")`` prints either ``+debug`` or ``~debug`` "
"depending on the name of the variant. Non-boolean variants print as "
"``name=value``. To print variant names or values independently, use ``spec."
"format(\"{variants.<name>.name}\")`` or ``spec.format(\"{variants.<name>."
"value}\")``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/spec.py:docstring of
#: spack.spec.Spec.format:57
msgid ""
"There are a few attributes on specs that can be specified as key-value pairs "
"that are *not* variants, e.g.: ``os``, ``arch``, ``architecture``, "
"``target``, ``namespace``, etc. You can format these with an optional "
"``key=`` prefix, e.g. ``{namespace=namespace}`` or ``{arch=architecture}``, "
"etc. The ``key=`` prefix will be colorized along with the value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/spec.py:docstring of
#: spack.spec.Spec.format:63
msgid ""
"When formatting specs, key-value pairs are separated from preceding parts of "
"the spec by whitespace. To avoid printing extra whitespace when the "
"formatted attribute is not set, you can add whitespace to the key *inside* "
"the braces of the format string, e.g.:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/spec.py:docstring of
#: spack.spec.Spec.format:68
msgid "{ namespace=namespace}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/spec.py:docstring of
#: spack.spec.Spec.format:72
msgid ""
"This evaluates to ``\" namespace=builtin\"`` if ``namespace`` is set to "
"``builtin``, and to ``\"\"`` if ``namespace`` is ``None``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/spec.py:docstring of
#: spack.spec.Spec.format:75
msgid ""
"Spec format strings use ``\\`` as the escape character. Use ``\\{`` and ``\\}"
"`` for literal braces, and ``\\\\`` for the literal ``\\`` character."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/spec.py:docstring of
#: spack.spec.Spec.format:78
msgid "string containing the format to be expanded"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/spec.py:docstring of
