#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/variant.py:docstring of
#: spack.variant.any_combination_of:1
msgid ""
"Multi-valued variant that allows either any combination of the specified "
"values, or none at all (using ``variant=none``). The literal value ``none`` "
"is used as sentinel for the empty set, since in the spec DSL we have to "
"always specify a value for a variant."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/variant.py:docstring of
#: spack.variant.any_combination_of:5 spack.variant.disjoint_sets:4
msgid ""
"It is up to the package implementation to handle the value ``none`` "
"specially, if at all."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/variant.py:docstring of
#: spack.variant.any_combination_of:7
msgid "See also :func:`auto_or_any_combination_of` and :func:`disjoint_sets`."
msgstr ""

